<p><a name="KDE_4.1" id="KDE_4.1"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=KDE_4&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: KDE 4.1">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">KDE 4.1</span></h2>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="/wiki/File:KDE_4-1_desktop.png" class="image" title="KDE 4.1 showing Kickoff and the folderview."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1b/KDE_4-1_desktop.png/300px-KDE_4-1_desktop.png" width="300" height="225" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:KDE_4-1_desktop.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
KDE 4.1 showing Kickoff and the folderview.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>KDE 4.1 was released on July 29 2008.<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_announcement_27-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_announcement-27" title=""><span>[</span>28<span>]</span></a></sup> KDE 4.1 includes a shared emoticon theming system which is used in PIM and Kopete, and DXS, a service that lets applications download and install data from the Internet with one click.<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_goals_28-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_goals-28" title=""><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup> Also introduced are <a href="/wiki/GStreamer" title="GStreamer">GStreamer</a>, <a href="/wiki/QuickTime" title="QuickTime">QuickTime</a> 7, and <a href="/wiki/DirectShow" title="DirectShow">DirectShow</a> 9 <a href="/wiki/Phonon_(KDE)" title="Phonon (KDE)">Phonon</a> backends.<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_goals_28-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_goals-28" title=""><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup> Plasma improvements include support for <a href="/wiki/Qt_(toolkit)" title="Qt (toolkit)">Qt</a> widgets and <a href="/wiki/WebKit" title="WebKit">WebKit</a> integration – allowing many Apple <a href="/wiki/Dashboard_(software)" title="Dashboard (software)">Dashboard</a> widgets to be displayed.<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_goals_28-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_goals-28" title=""><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup> There will also be ports of some applications to Windows and <a href="/wiki/Mac_OS_X" title="Mac OS X">Mac OS X</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_goals_28-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_goals-28" title=""><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>New applications include:<sup id="cite_ref-4.1_goals_28-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4.1_goals-28" title=""><span>[</span>29<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Dragon_Player" title="Dragon Player">Dragon Player</a> multimedia player (formerly Codeine)</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/KDE-PIM" title="KDE-PIM" class="mw-redirect">KDE-PIM</a> module, with some <a href="/wiki/Akonadi" title="Akonadi">Akonadi</a> functionality</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Skanlite&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Skanlite (page does not exist)">Skanlite</a> scanner application</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Step_(KDE)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Step (KDE) (page does not exist)">Step</a> physics simulator</li>
<li>Games - <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kdiamond&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kdiamond (page does not exist)">Kdiamond</a> (a <a href="/wiki/Bejeweled" title="Bejeweled">Bejeweled</a> clone), <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kollision&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kollision (page does not exist)">Kollision</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=Kubrick_(KDE)&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Kubrick (KDE) (page does not exist)">Kubrick</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=KsirK&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="KsirK (page does not exist)">KsirK</a>, <a href="/w/index.php?title=KBreakout&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="KBreakout (page does not exist)">KBreakout</a></li>
</ul>
