</tr>
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="background:#C0C0C0">4.0<sup id="cite_ref-34" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-34" title=""><span>[</span>35<span>]</span></a></sup></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background: #ececec; color: black; text-align: left; padding-left: 0.5em; font-weight: bold;" class="table-rh">April 2 2007</th>
<td>Subsystem Freeze<br />
From this date forward, no new KDE subsystem or major changes can be committed to kdelibs.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background: #ececec; color: black; text-align: left; padding-left: 0.5em; font-weight: bold;" class="table-rh">May 1 2007</th>
<td>kdelibs soft API Freeze<br />
The kdelibs API is "soft-frozen", meaning that changes can be made with the consent of the core developers.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background: #ececec; color: black; text-align: left; padding-left: 0.5em; font-weight: bold;" class="table-rh">May 11 2007</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/Software_release_life_cycle#Alpha" title="Software release life cycle">Alpha</a> 1</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background: #ececec; color: black; text-align: left; padding-left: 0.5em; font-weight: bold;" class="table-rh">June 1 2007</th>
<td>trunk/KDE is module frozen<br />
Trunk is frozen for new or resurrected applications.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th style="background: #ececec; color: black; text-align: left; padding-left: 0.5em; font-weight: bold;" class="table-rh">July 4 2007</th>
